uild, Progressive Democrat|accessdate=March 19, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Kendra Horn]], incumbent U.S. Representative\n\n====Primary Results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n|title=Democratic primary results\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n|candidate  = Tom Guild\n|party      = Democratic Party (United States)\n|votes      = \n|percentage =\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n|candidate  = [[Kendra Horn]] (incumbent)\n|party      = Democratic Party (United States)\n|votes      = \n|percentage =\n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n|votes=\n|percentage= 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===Republican primary===\n====Candidates====\n=====Declared=====\n*[[Janet Barresi]], former [[Oklahoma Superintendent of Public Instruction|Oklahoma Superintendent of Public Instruction]]<ref name=\"OK05GOP\">{{Cite news|title=Number of Oklahoma Republicans seeking to unseat Horn grows|url=https://www.apnews.com/f26bfc52287b4a63af5e7740aaf460da|accessdate=October 2, 2019|work=[[Associated Press]]|date=October 2, 2019}}</ref>\n*Charles Tuffy Pringle\n*David Hill, businessman<ref name=\"OK05GOP\"/>\n*[[Terry Neese]], entrepreneur and nominee for [[Lieutenant Governor of Oklahoma|Lieutenant Governor]] in 1990<ref>{{cite news |last1=Felder |first1=Ben |title=Neese becomes second Republican to seek 5th District seat |url=https://newsok.com/article/5629741/neese-becomes-second-republican-to-seek-5th-district-seat |accessdate=April 25, 2019 |publisher=The Oklahoman |date=April 25, 2019}}</ref>\n*Michael Ballard, veteran<ref>{{cite news |last1=Van Risseghem |first1=David |title=Neese & Ballard Join Race For Congress |url=https://www.soonerpolitics.org/editorial/neese-ballard-join-race-for-congress |accessdate=May 31, 2019 |publisher=Sooner Politics |date=April 27, 2019}}</ref>\n*Miles V. Rahimi, Navy Veteran and Community Organizer<ref>{{cite news|last1=Casteel |first=Chris |title=GOP Hopefuls Speak To Crowd Eager To Reclaim Congressional Seat |url=