steel |first1=Chris |title=Cornett won't seek congressional seat, sources say |url=https://oklahoman.com/article/5643573/cornett-wont-seek-congressional-seat-sources-say |website=The Oklahoman |accessdate=October 10, 2019 |date=October 10, 2019}}</ref>\n*Carol Hefner, Donald Trump\u2019s 2016 Oklahoma campaign manager<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n*Bob Mills, businessman & co-chair for Donald Trump's 2016 Campaign in Oklahoma<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n*[[Steve Russell (politician)|Steve Russell]], former U.S. Representative<ref>{{cite news|last1=Mutnick|first1=Ally|title=Inside the Midterms' Biggest House Upset|url=https://www.nationaljournal.com/s/674872/inside-the-midterms-biggest-house-upset|publisher=National Journal|date=November 26, 2018|accessdate=February 15, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Greg Treat]], president pro tempore of the [[Oklahoma Senate]]<ref name=\"OK05Hermes\">{{cite news|last1=Hermes|first1=Grant|title=Rep. Horn Being Targeted In 2020 Republican Campaign Plan|url=http://www.news9.com/story/39824282/rep-horn-being-targeted-in-2020-republican-campaign-plan|publisher=KWTV|date=January 21, 2019|accessdate=February 15, 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Primary Results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Republican primary results\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = [[Janet Barresi]]\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Charles Tuffy Pringle\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = David Hill\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = [[Terry Neese]]\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Michael Ballard\n| party = Republican Party (Uni