ites for 1st district candidates\n* [https://kojoforcongress.com/ Kojo Asamoa-Caesar (D) for Congress]\n* [https://www.hernforcongress.com/ Kevin Hern (R) for Congress]\n\n;Official campaign websites for 2nd district candidates\n* [https://www.silkforcongress.com/ Joseph Silk (R) for Congress]\n\n;Official campaign websites for 5th district candidates\n* [http://mikeballardforcongress.com/ Michael Ballard (R) for Congress]\n* [https://janet2020.com/ Janet Barresi (R) for Congress]\n* [https://biceforcongress.com/ Stephanie Bice (R) for Congress]\n* [https://www.davidgreene.me/ David Greene (R) for Congress]\n* [https://www.davidhillforok.com/ David Hill (R) for Congress]\n* [https://www.kendrahornforcongress.com/ Kendra Horn (D) for Congress]\n* [https://neeseforcongress.com/ Terry Neese (R) for Congress]\n* [https://www.vansantforcongress.com/ Merideth VanSant (R) for Congress]\n\n{{2020 United States elections}}\n\n[[Category:2020 United States House of Representatives elections|Oklahoma]]\n[[Category:United States House of Representatives elections in Oklahoma|2020]]\n[[Category:2020 Oklahoma elections|House]]\n{{Oklahoma-election-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox election\n| election_name      = 2020 United States House of Representatives elections in Oklahoma\n| country            = Oklahoma\n| type               = legislative\n| ongoing            = yes\n| previous_election  = 2018 United States House of Representatives elections in Oklahoma\n| previous_year      = 2018\n| next_election      = 2022 United States House of Representatives elections in Oklahoma\n| next_year          = 2022\n| seats_for_election = All 5 Oklahoma seats to the [[United States House of Representatives]]\n| election_date      = November 3, 2020\n| party1             = Republican Party (United States)\n| last_election1     = 4\n| seats1             = \n| seat_change1       = \n| popular_vote1      = \n| percentage1        = \n| swing1             = \n| party2             = Democratic Party (United States)\n| last_election2     = 1\n| seats2             = \n| seat_change2       = \n| popular_vote2      = \n| percentage2        = \n| swing2             = \n| map_image          = \n| map_caption        = \n}}\n{{Elections in Oklahoma}}\nThe '''2020 United States House of Representatives elections in Oklahoma''' will be held on November 3, 2020, to elect the five [[United States House of Representatives|U.S. Representatives]] from the [[U.S. state|state]] of [[Oklahoma]], one from each of the state's five [[Oklahoma's congressional districts|congressional districts]]. The elections will coincide with the [[2020 United States presidential election|2020 U.S. presidential election]], as well as [[2020 United States House of Representatives elections|other elections]] to the House of Representatives, [[2020 United States Senate elections|elections]] to the [[United States Senate]] and various [[2020 United States elections#State elections|state]] and [[2020 United States elections#Local elections|local elections]].\n{{toclimit|2}}\n\n==District 1==\n{{see also|Oklahoma's 1st congressional district}}\nThe 1st district is located in the [[Tulsa metropolitan area]] and includes [[Creek County, Oklahoma|Creek]], [[Rogers County, Oklahoma|Rogers]], [[Tulsa County, Oklahoma|Tulsa]], [[Wagoner County, Oklahoma|Wagoner]] and [[Washington County, Oklahoma|Washington]] counties. The incumbent is Republican [[Kevin Hern]], who had represented the district since 2018. He was re-elected with 60% in the general election.\n\n===Republican primary===\n====Candidates====\n====Declared====\n* [[Kevin Hern]], incumbent U.S. Representative\n\n====Primary Results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Republican primary results\n}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = [[Kevin Hern]] (incumbent)\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box to