ct encompasses [[Eastern Oklahoma|eastern Oklahoma]] including [[Choctaw Country]], [[Muskogee, Oklahoma|Muskogee]] and [[Tahlequah, Oklahoma|Tahlequah]]. The incumbent is Republican [[Markwayne Mullin]], who was re-elected with 65.0% of the vote in 2018.<ref name=\"HPVT\">{{cite web|last1=Wasserman|first1=David|last2=Flinn|first2=Ally|title=2018 House Popular Vote Tracker|url=https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1WxDaxD5az6kdOjJncmGph37z0BPNhV1fNAH_g7IkpC0/htmlview|publisher=Cook Political Report|date=November 7, 2018|accessdate=February 15, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Republican primary===\n====Candidates====\n=====Declared=====\n*[[Markwayne Mullin]], incumbent U.S. Representative\n*[[Joseph Silk (politician)|Joseph Silk]], state senator<ref>{{cite web |last1=Forman |first1=Carmen |title=State senator Joseph Silk seeks to unseat Markwayne Mullin |url=https://oklahoman.com/article/5643693/state-senator-joseph-silk-seeks-to-unseat-markwayne-mullin |website=The Oklahoman |accessdate=October 14, 2019 |date=October 11, 2019}}</ref>\n*Rhonda Hopkins <ref>https://www.ok.gov/elections/support/ok_filing_2020.html</ref>\n\n==== Endorsements ====\n{{Endorsements box\n|title=Markwayne Mullin\n|list=\n;U.S. Presidents\n* [[Donald Trump]], [[President of the United States]]<ref>{{cite web| title=Trump went on a mini-endorsement spree on Tuesday| url=https://www.politico.com/newsletters/morning-score/2019/12/18/the-impeachment-vote-whip-count-783830| publisher=Politico| date=December 18, 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n====Primary Results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Republican primary results\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = [[Markwayne Mullin]] (incumbent)\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = [[Joseph Silk (politician)|Joseph Silk]]\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate 