 97\">{{Harvard citation no brackets|Skirda|2004| p=97}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Skirda 100\">{{Harvard citation no brackets|Skirda|2004| p=100}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Skirda 318\">{{Harvard citation no brackets|Skirda|2004| p=318}}</ref>\n<!--\n<ref name=\"Azarov 8\">{{Harvard citation no brackets|Azarov|2008| p=8}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Azarov 9\">{{Harvard citation no brackets|Azarov|2008| p=9}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Azarov 15\">{{Harvard citation no brackets|Azarov|2008| p=15}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Azarov 16\">{{Harvard citation no brackets|Azarov|2008| p=16}}</ref>\n-->\n}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n{{Refbegin}}\n*{{cite book|ref=harv|last=Palij|first=Michael|authorlink=|title=[[The Anarchism of Nestor Makhno, 1918\u20131921]]|publisher=University of Washington Press|location=Seattle, WA. United states|year=1976|isbn=0-295-95511-2|oclc=2372742}}\n*{{cite book|ref=harv|last=Archibald|first=Malcolm|url=http://www.nestormakhno.info/english/marusya.htm|title=Atamansha: the Story of Maria Nikiforova, the Anarchist Joan of Arc|publisher=Black Cat Press|location=Dublin|year=2007|isbn=978-0-9737827-0-7|oclc=239359065}}\n*{{cite book|ref=harv|last=Skirda|first=Alexandre|url=|title=Nestor Makhno: Anarchy's Cossack, the struggle for free Soviets in the Ukraine 1917-1921|publisher=AK Press|location=Oakland, Ca. United States|year=2004|isbn=978-1-902593-68-5|oclc=1902593685}}\n<!--\n*{{cite book|ref=harv|last=Azarov|first=Vyacheslav|others=trans. Archibald, Malcolm|title=Kontrrazvedka: The Story of the Makhnovist Intelligence Service|publisher=Black Cat Press|location=Edmonton, Alberta. Canada|year=2008|isbn=0-295-95511-2|oclc=2372742}}\n-->\n{{Refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote-inline}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://recollectionbooks.com/bleed/Encyclopedia/NikiforovaMaria.htm|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151209203210/http://recollectionbooks.com/bleed/Encyclopedia/NikiforovaMaria.htm|archivedate=2015-12-09|title=Maria Nikiforova|publisher=Daily Bleed|work=Anarchist Encyclopedia|