e: Group Theory] This package brings together all the articles on group theory from ''Plus'', the online mathematics magazine produced by the Millennium Mathematics Project at the University of Cambridge, exploring applications and recent breakthroughs, and giving explicit definitions and examples of groups.\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Group theory| ]]\n\n[[ml:\u0d17\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d42\u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d2a\u0d4d \u0d38\u0d3f\u0d26\u0d4d\u0d27\u0d3e\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d02]]\n", "name_user": "Acharyanarayan010", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eChemistry and materials science", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Group_theory"}
